JSON config

Type: object

JSON config file for fastfetch. Usually located at ~/.config/fastfetch/config.jsonc

No Additional Properties

$schema

root $schema
Type: string Default: "https://github.com/fastfetch-cli/fastfetch/raw/dev/doc/json_schema.json"

JSON schema URL, for JSON validation and IDE intelligence

logo

root logo

Fastfetch logo configurations
See also https://github.com/fastfetch-cli/fastfetch/wiki/Logo-options

Option 1

root logo oneOf item 0
Type: const

Disable logo

Specific value: null

Option 2

root logo oneOf item 1
Type: string

Set the source file of the logo

Option 3

root logo oneOf item 2
Type: object

Fastfetch logo configurations

No Additional Properties

type

root logo oneOf item 2 type
Type: enum (of string) Default: "auto"

Set the type of the logo

Must be one of:

  • "auto"
  • "builtin"
  • "small"
  • "file"
  • "file-raw"
  • "data"
  • "data-raw"
  • "sixel"
  • "kitty"
  • "kitty-direct"
  • "kitty-icat"
  • "iterm"
  • "chafa"
  • "raw"
  • "none"

root logo oneOf item 2 source
Type: string

Set the source file of the logo

chafa

root logo oneOf item 2 chafa
Type: object

Chafa configuration. See chafa documentation for details

No Additional Properties

fgOnly

root logo oneOf item 2 chafa fgOnly
Type: boolean Default: false

Produce character-cell output using foreground colors only

symbols

root logo oneOf item 2 chafa symbols
Type: string

Specify character symbols to employ in final output

canvasMode

root logo oneOf item 2 chafa canvasMode
Type: enum (of string)

Determine how colors are used in the output. This value maps to enum ChafaCanvasMode.

Must be one of:

  • "TRUECOLOR"
  • "INDEXED_256"
  • "INDEXED_240"
  • "INDEXED_16"
  • "FGBG_BGFG"
  • "FGBG"
  • "INDEXED_8"
  • "INDEXED_16_8"

colorSpace

root logo oneOf item 2 chafa colorSpace
Type: enum (of string)

Set color space used for quantization. This value maps to enum ChafaColorSpace.

Must be one of:

  • "RGB"
  • "DIN99D"

ditherMode

root logo oneOf item 2 chafa ditherMode
Type: enum (of string)

Set output dither mode (No effect with 24-bit color). This value maps to enum ChafaDitherMode.

Must be one of:

  • "NONE"
  • "ORDERED"
  • "DIFFUSION"

general

root general
Type: object

Fastfetch general configurations

No Additional Properties

thread

root general thread
Type: boolean Default: true

Use separate threads for HTTP requests

escapeBedrock

root general escapeBedrock
Type: boolean Default: true

On Bedrock Linux, whether to escape the bedrock jail

playerName

root general playerName
Type: string

The name of the player to use for Media and Player modules. Linux only

dsForceDrm

root general dsForceDrm
Default: false

Force display detection to use DRM. Linux only

Option 1

root general dsForceDrm oneOf item 0
Type: const

Try wayland, then x11, then drm

Specific value: false

Option 2

root general dsForceDrm oneOf item 1
Type: const

Use /sys/class/drm only

Specific value: "sysfs-only"

Option 3

root general dsForceDrm oneOf item 2
Type: const

Try libdrm first, then sysfs if libdrm fails

Specific value: true

wmiTimeout

root general wmiTimeout
Type: integer Default: 5000

Set the timeout (ms) for WMI queries, -1 for no timeout. Windows only

processingTimeout

root general processingTimeout
Type: integer Default: 5000

Set the timeout (ms) when waiting for child processes, -1 for no timeout

preRun

root general preRun
Type: string Default: ""

Set the command to be executed before printing logos

detectVersion

root general detectVersion
Type: boolean Default: true

Whether to detect and display component versions. Mainly for benchmarking

size

root display size
Type: object

Set how size values should be displayed

No Additional Properties

binaryPrefix

root display size binaryPrefix
Default: "iec"

Set the binary prefix to use when formatting sizes

Option 1

root display size binaryPrefix oneOf item 0
Type: const

1024 Bytes = 1 KiB, 1024 KiB = 1 MiB, ... (standard)

Specific value: "iec"

Option 2

root display size binaryPrefix oneOf item 1
Type: const

1000 Bytes = 1 kB, 1000 kB = 1 MB, ...

Specific value: "si"

Option 3

root display size binaryPrefix oneOf item 2
Type: const

1024 Bytes = 1 KB, 1024 KB = 1 MB, ...

Specific value: "jedec"

maxPrefix

root display size maxPrefix
Type: enum (of string) Default: "YB"

Set the largest binary prefix to use when formatting sizes

Must be one of:

  • "B"
  • "kB"
  • "MB"
  • "GB"
  • "TB"
  • "PB"
  • "EB"
  • "ZB"
  • "YB"

ndigits

root display size ndigits
Type: integer Default: 2

Set the number of digits to keep after the decimal point when formatting sizes

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 9

Type: object

Set how percentage values should be displayed

No Additional Properties

type

root display percent type
Type: object

Set the percentage output type

Option 1

root display percent type oneOf item 0
Type: number Default: 9

0 to use global setting, 1 for percentage number, 2 for multi-color bar, 3 for both, 6 for bar only, 9 for colored number, 10 for monochrome bar

Value must be greater or equal to 0 and lesser or equal to 255

Option 2

root display percent type oneOf item 1
Type: array of enum (of string) Default: ["num", "num-color"]

Array of string flags

No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root display percent type oneOf item 1 item 1 items
Type: enum (of string)

Must be one of:

  • "num"
  • "bar"
  • "hide-others"
  • "num-color"
  • "bar-monochrome"

format

root modules modules items anyOf item 1 oneOf Battery format
Type: string

Output format of the module Battery. See Wiki for formatting syntax
1. {manufacturer}: Battery manufacturer
2. {model-name}: Battery model name
3. {technology}: Battery technology
4. {capacity}: Battery capacity (percentage num)
5. {status}: Battery status
6. {temperature}: Battery temperature (formatted)
7. {cycle-count}: Battery cycle count
8. {serial}: Battery serial number
9. {manufacture-date}: Battery manufactor date
10. {capacity-bar}: Battery capacity (percentage bar)
11. {time-days}: Battery time remaining days
12. {time-hours}: Battery time remaining hours
13. {time-minutes}: Battery time remaining minutes
14. {time-seconds}: Battery time remaining seconds
